Does this differ by country?


Not really.
Disgust domain and country interact to predict choices in the dating game, F(2,2028) = 21.36, p = p<.001

However, the three-way interaction between disgust domain, country, and sex was not significant.

Does disgust sensitivity predict game choices?


Yes.

For all domains, greater disgust sensitivity predicts less frequently choosing that domain

Do own traits predict the traits chosen?


For some.


People who rated themselves higher in artistic ability (b = 0.0968174, p = p<.001) or sexiness (b = 0.0462741, p = 0.039) were more likely to choose these traits. However, people who rated themselves higher in kindness were less likely to choose kindness options (b = -0.0368813, p = 0.032).
